More and more forces mobilized for giant strike
On Friday, the League of Trade Unions and the Hungarian Federation of Trade Unions form their coordination committee for the indefinite strike that begins on Monday.
On Saturday a large protest assembly will be held, on Monday - on the day of the referendum on the Health Insurance Act - the work resignation begins.
It is expected that there will be strike-related, significant traffic impediments, since railway transport is almost completely discontinued, and also the Budapest public transport companies (BKV) will strike until 1 p.m.
