Cuba still offers a bite that is unique in the world and especially attracts railroad lovers.
The sugar cane from remote plantations brought steam and diesel-powered narrow lanes to the sugar factories.
Their fleet has not been renewed for decades, and so you can see nice and fully functioning locomotives, whose peers have long been in the museum elsewhere.
Excursion destinations
