All that remains to be mentioned is that the above-mentioned property of Hemingways has a museum whose visit should not be missed by anyone who likes this writer.
The Vi<0xC3><0xB1>ales valley in the west of the island is one of the most picturesque corners of Cuba.
The lush vegetation grows on limestone soil.
The Mogotas, limestone hills and rocks, rise steeply from the valley floor, in their cavities accumulated fertile soil, through which also weathered rock areas are covered by dense growth.
This valley is where perhaps the best Cuban tobacco is grown.
In its final form, you can meet him when you visit one of Havana’s cigar factories.
It may also seem interesting to some that the Chilean episode of the television series "Major Zeman" was shot there.
Trinidad (disambiguation)
An ancient city founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
Fame and wealth brought her the trade in slaves and sugar.
The wealth embodied in the adorable beauty of the small town.
Spanish colonial architecture, heavily influenced by the later French settlers, has hardly changed in the last four hundred years.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray Mountains, is such a remote place that there was no road that would have connected the area to the rest of the country in the 1950s.
This insulation contributed to the fact that it was left unnoticed.
Nothing was built there, but therefore nothing torn down, everyone was glad that he had a roof over his head.
If you have more than one afternoon to spend in Trinidad, it’s worth visiting interesting places in the area, such as Playa Ancón beach or the “Valley of Sugar Mills”.
In the evening you should then go to the Casa de la Música, which revives after dark, and where the music does not remain silent until the morning.
Baracoa
