There the best chocolate is made, in the church you can see the cross of Columbus (in reality it was created about a hundred years after the trips of Columbus), and from the hill where stands the former castle, the current Hotel El Castillo, you can see several table mountains, of which El Yunque is the most famous.
About the coffee, the rum, the cigars, the Sierra Maestra mountains, the pork bay and the island of Pinos, about the Tropicana cabaret, the sanctuary of the Cuban patron Caridad del Cobre, about the Santeria, an African religion to which the descendants of slaves confess, you could write many pages.
