Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, such as age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, one has to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract stating that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to provide the corresponding compensation amount in case of damages.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance consisting of several factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions will also be due.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same is true for married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also thoroughly study the situation in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance in order to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under 25 years of age encounter numerous obstacles when choosing a low-priced insurance, such as the low driving practice and the young driving license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance coverage to take out full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full insurance with deductible, so that while the benefits of a full insurance are covered, they are offered at a low price.
This type of contract involves the customer having to pay part of the amount incurred by the damage themselves.
The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s principal representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage incurred on his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under the age of 25, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs; this increases your credit by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic rate at the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a high-yield year behind it can afford to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract, as the accident rate drops as driving practice increases.
Thus, it is most sensible to opt for full insurance with self-deductibility.
Normally, young people cannot take advantage of their previous experience, either in the event of an accident or at the time of driving, explains the Spanish director of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the beginner’s fear has been dropped.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out a full insurance policy; of course only if the financial situation of the appropriate person also allows.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full insurance insurance with self-deductible (for an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which is only used for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to set up a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For retirees it is advisable to take out a full insurance with self-deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only applies with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accidental damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
